  "body": "For comparison, the chart with moving average of 1000 looks like this:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13686139/70396912-29670f00-1a05-11ea-884a-dd8ae2d5f8d4.png)\r\n\r\nand without moving average, like this:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13686139/70396918-371c9480-1a05-11ea-9e7e-bfcdd0e75cc2.png)\r\n\r\nthe second chart, while showing the great variance, lets the components occlude each other, thus reducing the utility of the chart. It would be better to replace it with percentile charts. More thoughts on what these percentile charts show, are needed",
